  "timeframe": "4H / 15M",
  "market_context": "USDCAD on the 4-hour shows a consolidation around 1.4090–1.4120 with repeated highs failing to form protected swings. An open range low near 1.4080 remains as an untapped target below the consolidation.",
  "key_observation": "Within the 4H consolidation, price could not form continuation closures to protect new highs, signaling that the previous high would likely be swept before reversing lower to the open range low target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the 4-hour consolidation and note the open range low has not been hit, leaving a downside target.",
    "Recognize that price cannot form continuation closures or protected swings off new highs, confirming ongoing consolidation.",
    "Anticipate a sweep of the previous high followed by a reversal lower; small wick allows trading the reversal candle, large wick means waiting for the next candle.",
    "Drop to the 15-minute timeframe to find precise entry on the sweep.",
    "Observe price run into the high but wait for a closure through / change in state of delivery to confirm the wick formation.",
    "After the closure confirms, enter short with stop above the swept high, targeting the 4H range low, with SMT divergence pairing the candle 2 entry."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade worked out — clean reversal off the previous candle's high paired with change in state of delivery and SMT, expanding toward the range low target.",
  "lessons": "The fractal model pairs 4H bias with 15M execution: consolidation without protected swings telegraphs a liquidity sweep, and waiting for CISD plus SMT on the LTF provides high-probability reversal entries with defined risk.",
